The paper analyzes international co-authorship relations in the Social Science Citation Index, which involves social science research and citation analysis. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category. The paper also uses network statistics and information theory, which could fall under cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses collaborations and partnerships, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy).
